28
00:01:50,665 --&gt; 00:01:55,703
In the &quot;Shuowen Jiezi&quot;, the meanings of the Yin and Yang were more clearly explained

29
00:01:56,535 --&gt; 00:01:59,961
such as the sentence - &quot;Ying, which means dark, refers to the southern part of a river and the northern part of a mountain&quot;

30
00:02:00,193 --&gt; 00:02:02,618
which is the same with the sentence above-mentioned.

31
00:02:03,404 --&gt; 00:02:06,522
The difference between Yin and Yang is related to the geographical features in Central China.

32
00:02:06,794 --&gt; 00:02:13,886
Both the southern part of a mountain and the northern part of a river are easier to be exposed to the sunshine, so it's warm there which is meant by Yang.

33
00:02:14,305 --&gt; 00:02:21,029
however, the opposite two parts are relatively cooler,

34
00:02:21,725 --&gt; 00:02:23,639
so they belong to Ying.

35
00:02:24,153 --&gt; 00:02:30,708
Besides, many geographical names are related to the Thought of Yin and Yang.

36
00:02:31,176 --&gt; 00:02:34,635
For instance, &quot;Hua Ying&quot; is the northern part of Huashan Mountain.

37
00:02:35,054 --&gt; 00:02:37,547
and &quot;Heng Yang&quot; means the southern part of Hengshan Mountain.

38
00:02:37,960 --&gt; 00:02:41,461
